```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "memory": "32gb",
      "tasks": 1,
      "cpus_per_task": 8,
      "gpus": 1,
      "partition": "main"
    },
    "job_name": "udal",
    "output_file": "/mnt/work/dhuseljic/logs/udal/evaluation/%A_%a__%x.log",
    "array_tasks": "1-10%2",
    "environment": "dal-toolbox",
    "script": "evaluate.py",
    "script_arguments": {
      "model": "resnet18",
      "dataset": "CIFAR100",
      "dataset_path": "/mnt/work/dhuseljic/datasets",
      "queried_indices_json": "/mnt/work/dhuseljic/results/udal/active_learning/${dataset}/${model}/${al_strat}/N_INIT${n_init}__ACQ_SIZE${acq_size}__N_ACQ${n_acq}/seed${random_seed}/queried_indices.json",
      "output_dir": "/mnt/work/dhuseljic/results/udal/evaluation/${dataset}/${model}/${al_strat}/N_INIT${n_init}__ACQ_SIZE${acq_size}__N_ACQ${n_acq}/seed${random_seed}/",
      "random_seed": "$SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID"
    }
  }
}
```

The script utilizes **Slurm** as a workload manager, which is commonly used for running high-performance computing jobs. The script requests specific resources, such as memory, CPU cores, GPUs, and a specific partition. It also defines the job name, output file, and an array of tasks to be run. The script then activates the `dal-toolbox` environment and runs a Python script called `evaluate.py` with several arguments that specify the model, dataset, and other settings.
